cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new objective function and a decoding algorithm, which are related to optimization and search, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The proposed model is based on neural networks, which are a type of computational model, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed model to the WMT German/English and French/English tasks, which involve image captioning, speech recognition, and machine translation, among other tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible category.
